Program_Policies: A grade of C or better is required for all courses in the minor, as specified by Senate Policy 59-10. In addition, at least six credits of the minor must be unique from the prescribed courses required by a student's major(s).; A student may not use credit for BISC 1 or BISC 2 along with credit for BIOL 11 and BIOL 12, or BIOL 110.; A student may not use credit for CHEM 1 or CHEM 3 along with credit for CHEM 110 and CHEM 111 or CHEM 112 and CHEM 113.; A student may not use credit for PHYS 1 along with credit for PHYS 250 or PHYS 251.; A student may not use credit for MICRB 106 and MICRB 107 along with credit for MICRB 201 and MICRB 202.
